4 (5) Money in the fund may be expended, upon appropriation, as
5 follows:
6 (a) Not more than $1,400,000.00 $1,700,000.00 annually may be
7 expended for the administrative costs of the department and the
8 board in implementing this part and part 361.
9 (b) After expenditures for the administrative costs under
10 subdivision (a), money in the fund may be used, expended, upon
11 approval of the board, to provide grants to local units of
12 government pursuant to section 36203.
13 (c) After If, after expenditures under subdivisions (a) and
14 (b), have been made, if the amount of money remaining in the fund
15 exceeds $5,000,000.00, money in the fund may be used, expended,
16 upon approval of the board, pursuant to part 361 for the purchase
17 of development rights to farmland or the acquisition of
18 agricultural conservation easements.
19 (6) Expenditures of money in the fund as provided in this part
20 are consistent with the state's interest in preserving farmland and
21 are for an important public purpose.
